The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 October is 86,028 (9,915.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 October, there were 3,400 new confirmed cases (391.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 October, there were 2,578 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 32% (822 extra cases).
